    <item>
      <title>Xrow-Product-class essential functions issues and/or bugs</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/xrowecommerce/forum/bug_tracker/xrow_product_class_essential_functions_issues_and_or_bugs</link>
      <description>1. Xrow Product Options displays autoprice function for currency but without function.&#13;
&#13;
How to reproduce: Use a min. 2-language setup. Define the main currency, i.e Euro for ger-DE, fre-FR and on the other hand GBP for eng-GB. Choose the product "Beer" which is part of the installations democontent. Add this to the basket and enter quantity of various items.The baskets total amount in Euro seems to be calculated correctly. When calling the basket in the second currency (i.e. by switching the language ger-DE-Euro to eng-GB-GBP) only the product's base price is tooken in account and displayed correctly in GBP. Obviously the prices for all options are set to 0.00 GBP and calculated so on.&#13;
&#13;
2 In addition there is another issue that can be observed similarly: The weight values entered in Xrow-product-class-Options are also not tooken in account. Allthough entering a value per each option, the calculation of the shipping weight per option item is apparently made and calculated by admitting zero values. &#13;
&#13;
3 Unfortunately the datatype "options" is not supporting search functions. So the great feature of xrow-product-class for adding extensive description per each option, can be a great problem in a real store, which is hardly limiting the usability. &#13;
&#13;
4. The weight unit (i.e. kg/lbs) and the unit names seem to be not really implemented. No settings and no (variable) calculation parameters could be found. The unit's name seems to be purely based on the template level.&#13;
&#13;
Since there is no implemention, the whole lot of all fine stuff that is depending on product options is useless.</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Gerhard Drisch)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/xrowecommerce/forum/bug_tracker/xrow_product_class_essential_functions_issues_and_or_bugs</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 05 Aug 2011 09:22:43 +0000</pubDate>
